   <conbody>
      <hazardstatement type="note" class="+ topic/note hazard-d/hazardstatement ">
         <messagepanel class="+ topic/ul hazard-d/messagepanel ">
            <typeofhazard class="+ topic/li hazard-d/typeofhazard "/>
            <howtoavoid class="+ topic/li hazard-d/howtoavoid ">When the manual bypass switch is in <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Bypass</b> position,
it is not possible for the system to automatically switch back to
inverter operation in case the bypass mains becomes unavailable.</howtoavoid>
         </messagepanel>
      </hazardstatement>
      <section class="- topic/section ">
         <sectiondiv class="- topic/sectiondiv ">
            <note class="- topic/note ">The bypass mains needs to be available
and within tolerance. The static switch EN (BYP SSW) needs to be available.
The switch over do not interrupt to the load.</note>
         </sectiondiv>
      </section>
      <section class="- topic/section ">
         <title class="- topic/title ">How to Check the Function of the ISBS Controller</title>
         <ol class="- topic/ol ">
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p ">Check that the system is in normal operation and that no alarms
are active.</p>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p ">Switch to bypass operation:</p>
               <note class="- topic/note ">The bypass mains needs
to be available and within tolerance. The static switch EN (BYP SSW)
needs to be available.</note>
               <ol conref="1220236_How_to_Switch_from_Normal_Operation_to_Bypass_Operation_CPT_DD00545782.dita#HowToSwitchFromNormalOperationToByp-5AF57FF1/Switch-to-bypass_1220236"
                   class="- topic/ol ">
                  <li class="- topic/li "/>
               </ol>
            </li>
            <li otherprops="2pMBS" class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p ">Check that the EN (BYP SSW) input switch
and the external bypass input switch are closed. Turn the manual bypass
switch to the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Bypass</b> position.</p>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p ">Check the status of all indication LEDs on the ISBS controller
(A703) is ok:<ul class="- topic/ul ">
                     <li class="- topic/li ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">The STATUS_1 LED should be flashing slowly (0.5 Hz).</p>
                     </li>
                     <li class="- topic/li ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">The STATUS_3 LED should be turned off.</p>
                     </li>
                     <li class="- topic/li ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">The 15V FAN LED is not used.</p>
                     </li>
                     <li class="- topic/li ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">All other LEDs should be turned on.</p>
                     </li>
                  </ul>For more information about the LEDs see the chapter <i class="+ topic/ph hi-d/i ">Troubleshooting
the ISBS</i> in the <i class="+ topic/ph hi-d/i ">Operating Manual</i>.</p>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p ">Monitor the system output voltage before the manual bypass
switch.</p>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p ">Press the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Reset button</b> on the controller (A070).</p>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p ">Check that:<ul class="- topic/ul ">
                     <li class="- topic/li ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">The ISBS controller (A703) switched to independent fire.</p>
                     </li>
                     <li class="- topic/li ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">The STATUS_3 LED is turned on.</p>
                     </li>
                     <li class="- topic/li ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">The STATUS_1 LED is flashing very fast (4Hz).</p>
                     </li>
                     <li class="- topic/li ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">The output is supplied over the static switch EN (BYP SSW).</p>
                     </li>
                     <li class="- topic/li ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">The break in output voltage &lt; 20ms.</p>
                     </li>
                     <li class="- topic/li ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">The <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Display</b> shows <codeph class="+ topic/ph pr-d/codeph ">Standby</codeph>.</p>
                     </li>
                     <li class="- topic/li ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">It is not possible to turn the system on by pressing the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">On button</b> on the front panel. The system should be locked in
ISBS operation.</p>
                     </li>
                  </ul>
               </p>
            </li>
            <li otherprops="2pMBS" class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p ">Open the EN (BYP SSW) input switch to disconnect
the bypass supply.</p>
            </li>
            <li platform="WxW" class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p ">Open the inverter input switch to disconnect
the DC power supply.</p>
            </li>
            <li platform="WxW" class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p ">Discharge the DC capacitor by keeping the charging/discharge
switch in position 1 until the warning LED turns off.</p>
            </li>
         </ol>
      </section>
      <section class="- topic/section ">
         <title class="- topic/title ">Restart the System</title>
         <p class="- topic/p ">After the function of
the ISBS have been tested and the controller board have been reset
the system can be started again. To restart the system:</p>
         <ol conref="1220236_How_to_Switch_from_ISS_or_ISBS_Operation_to_Normal_Operation_CPT_DD00545783.dita#HowToSwitchFromISSOrISBSOperationTo-5AEB8E5E/ISBS-restart_1220236"
             class="- topic/ol ">
            <li class="- topic/li "/>
         </ol>
         <p class="- topic/p ">The system is in normal operation and the load is supplied
by the system.</p>
      </section>
